race.comment: DEAMBER (3) was outclassed in the Jungle Mist Classic last start but wasn't far away in Saturday grade prior to that. She drops back to country level now third-up into the campaign and the rise to 1400m is a big tick for her. Should be hitting her peak now third-up and can end her winning drought. CAVALLO RED (6) has been close in metropolitan races recently, including a 1MW event on a Saturday last time out. Likely to settle in the second half of the field but has showed his class in recent efforts and he looks well placed in this race. GOLD KEEPER (4) comes here third-up after a nice run in a $40k race last time out where he hit the line nicely. Third-up now and drawn much better, he looks open to further improvement. Can play a leading role. PATCHWORK (5) can improve today getting back out in distance. DIVINE INANNA (7) is better than she showed last time out and looks open to sharp improvement.
